FIG. 1 is a cross sectional view of a finished magnetic disc, greatly exaggerated in thickness, showing a central hard core substrate and an overlying smoothing layer, constructed in accordance with the present invention. Additionally there are a magnetic medium layer, a finishing layer, and a read-write head mounted on a slider;


FIG. 2 is an enlarged cross sectional view of a segment of a rigid disc substrate showing a central hard core substrate and a smoothing layer that is as formed (A) and as smoothed (B); and


FIG. 3 is an enlarged cross sectional view of a segment of a finished magnetic disc, showing a central hard core substrate, a texturized overlying smoothing layer--constructed in accordance with the present invention, a magnetic medium layer and a smoothing layer.
